LAUNCH
  Fire missiles or launch satellites.

SYNTAX
  launch <plane-spec> <target-x,y>
  lnch   <plane-spec> <target-x,y>

DESCRIPTION
  Launches missiles at a target or puts satellites into orbit.
  Only missile-type planes (built with missile capability) can
  be launched.

  Missiles are destroyed on use.  They deal significant damage
  to the target sector's efficiency and population.

  Satellites are not destroyed; they enter orbit and can provide
  intelligence (visible to the owning country).

  Missiles require:
    - At least 40% efficiency
    - Enough fuel (petrol) for flight

EXAMPLE
  launch 5 -4,2             fire missile (plane 5) at sector -4,2
  launch 10 0,0             launch satellite (plane 10) into orbit

SEE ALSO
  bomb  fly  mission  build  show
